tom two-thirds of the nori sheet, leaving top one-third free. Spread 1 heaped tablespoon of the avocado mixture in a line across cauliflower at the end closest to you. Layer 4 pieces of the capsicum, 4 pieces of the cabbage and 4 pieces of the spring onions\/shallots onto avocado mixture. Brush the top edge of nori sheet with water. Using the bamboo sushi mat, begin rolling tightly from the bottom up to form a roll. Allow to sit for 1-2 minutes, seam side down, then slice into 6 pieces. Repeat with remaining nori sheets, cauliflower, avocado mixture and vegetables (makes 6 rolls in total)."},{"isHeader":true,"content":"Peanut dipping sauce"},{"content":"Place peanuts into mixing bowl and chop <b>5 sec\/speed 7<b>. Scrape down sides of mixing bowl with spatula, then transfer 2 teaspoons of the chopped peanuts into a small bowl and set aside."},{"content":"Add water, syrup, tamari and Sriracha and blend <b>1 min\/speed 10<b>. Transfer into a small dipping bowl, sprinkle with reserved chopped peanuts and serve with sushi."}],"hintsAndTricks":["Be sure to check the label of your tamari, as not all brands are gluten free."],"basicInfo":["easy","30m","50m","6 portions"]}